# Knowledge capture config (personal)

## Push destination
<!-- Where to send captured learning notes. Options: -->
<!-- - Capacities (macOS, requires desktop app running) -->
<!-- - Obsidian (via file write) -->
<!-- - Local file only (default fallback) -->

## Push method
<!-- For Capacities, use X-Callback URL: -->
<!--
python3 -c "
import urllib.parse
title = '''[TITLE]'''
body = '''[MARKDOWN BODY]'''
capacities_type = '[note|definition|page]'
url = f'capacities://x-callback-url/createNewObject?spaceId=YOUR_SPACE_ID&typeKeyword={capacities_type}&title={urllib.parse.quote(title)}&mdContent={urllib.parse.quote(body)}'
print(url)
" | xargs open
-->
<!-- Replace YOUR_SPACE_ID with your Capacities space ID. -->

## Capacities type mapping

| Note type | typeKeyword |
|-----------|-------------|
| Atomic note | note |
| Definition | definition |
| Page | page |

## Fallback

If push destination is not available, save to `~/knowledge/learned-today.md` with YAML frontmatter.
